{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"language":"python","display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.12","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":15259950,"datasetId":9762220,"databundleVersionId":16158818}],"dockerImageVersionId":31286,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Project Title : Drone Detection System for Surveillance","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\nimport warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T13:53:50.085732Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T13:53:50.086000Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.265922Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T13:53:50.085968Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.265039Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":1},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Problem Statement : \n### With the increasing use of drones in unauthorized and potentially harmful activities, detecting drones in surveillance environments has become a critical challenge. Traditional monitoring systems struggle to differentiate drones from similar entities such as birds or aircraft, especially under noisy environmental conditions.\n\n### This project aims to develop an intelligent multi-modal detection system that identifies drones using both:\n\n### Visual data (video frames)\n\n### Acoustic signals (audio recordings)\n\n### The system will:\n\n* ### Detect and classify flying objects (drone vs bird vs aircraft)\n\n* ### Use audio signals to validate or reject visual detections\n\n* ### Reduce false positives caused by birds or environmental noise\n\n* ### Generate prioritized alerts for potential threats","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import os\n\naudio_path = \"/kaggle/input/datasets/partar/drone-detection-dont-upload/Audio/Audio\"\nvideo_path = \"/kaggle/input/datasets/partar/drone-detection-dont-upload/Video/Video\"\n\naudio_files = os.listdir(audio_path)\nvideo_files = os.listdir(video_path)\n\naudio_data = []\nvideo_data = []\n\n# Extract Audio files.\n\nfor file in audio_files:\n    if file.endswith(\".wav\"):\n        label = file.split('_')[0]\n        full_path = os.path.join(audio_path, file)\n        audio_data.append((full_path, label))\n\n# Extract Video files.\n\nfor file in video_files:\n    if file.endswith('.mp4'):\n        label = file.split('_')[1]\n        full_path = os.path.join(video_path, file)\n        video_data.append((full_path, label))","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.268084Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.268523Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.318267Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.268492Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.317275Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":2},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **Extract both audio and video file path and save it to \"audio_data\" and \"video_data\" respectivly.**\n\n#### **This files are saved in the form of list.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Created Datasets.\n\naudio_df = pd.DataFrame(audio_data, columns = ['Path', 'Class'])\nvideo_df = pd.DataFrame(video_data, columns = ['Path', 'Class'])","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.319830Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.320339Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.327800Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.320272Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.326873Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":3},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# make Label \"Threat\" if class is \"DRONE\" else \"Non-Threat\" in both audio and video data\n\naudio_df['Label'] = audio_df['Class'].apply(lambda x : \"Threat\" if x == 'DRONE' else \"Non-Threat\")\nvideo_df['Label'] = video_df['Class'].apply(lambda x : \"Threat\" if x == 'DRONE' else \"Non-Threat\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.328735Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.328999Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.353227Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.328975Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T13:53:51.352332Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":4},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **Make label \"Threat\" if drone detected otherwise \"None-Threat\"**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"audio_df.head()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T07:59:00.622711Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T07:59:00.623108Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T07:59:00.658012Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T07:59:00.623084Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T07:59:00.657165Z"}},"outputs":[{"execution_count":5,"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":"                                                Path       Class       Label\n0  /kaggle/input/datasets/partar/drone-detection-...  BACKGROUND  Non-Threat\n1  /kaggle/input/datasets/partar/drone-detection-...       DRONE      Threat\n2  /kaggle/input/datasets/partar/drone-detection-...       DRONE      Threat\n3  /kaggle/input/datasets/partar/drone-detection-...  HELICOPTER  Non-Threat\n4  /kaggle/input/datasets/partar/drone-detection-...       DRONE      Threat","text/html":"<div>\n<style scoped>\n    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n        vertical-align: middle;\n    }\n\n    .dataframe tbody tr th {\n        vertical-align: top;\n    }\n\n    .dataframe thead th {\n        text-align: right;\n    }\n</style>\n<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n  <thead>\n    <tr style=\"text-align: right;\">\n      <th></th>\n      <th>Path</th>\n      <th>Class</th>\n      <th>Label</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <th>0</th>\n      <td>/kaggle/input/datasets/partar/drone-detection-...</td>\n      <td>BACKGROUND</td>\n      <td>Non-Threat</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>1</th>\n      <td>/kaggle/input/datasets/partar/drone-detection-...</td>\n      <td>DRONE</td>\n      <td>Threat</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>2</th>\n      <td>/kaggle/input/datasets/partar/drone-detection-...</td>\n      <td>DRONE</td>\n      <td>Threat</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>3</th>\n      <td>/kaggle/input/datasets/partar/drone-detection-...</td>\n      <td>HELICOPTER</td>\n      <td>Non-Threat</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th>4</th>\n      <td>/kaggle/input/datasets/partar/drone-detection-...</td>\n      <td>DRONE</td>\n      <td>Threat</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n</div>"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":5},{"cell_type":"code","source":"audio_df.info()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T13:54:04.224394Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T13:54:04.225078Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T13:54:04.243888Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T13:54:04.225046Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T13:54:04.242694Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"<class 'pandas.core.frame.DataFrame'>\nRangeIndex: 90 entries, 0 to 89\nData columns (total 3 columns):\n #   Column  Non-Null Count  Dtype \n---  ------  --------------  ----- \n 0   Path    90 non-null     object\n 1   Class   90 non-null     object\n 2   Label   90 non-null     object\ndtypes: object(3)\nmemory usage: 2.2+ KB\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":5},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### There are just 90 audio data in audio file.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"video_df.info()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T13:54:18.334938Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T13:54:18.335394Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T13:54:18.348088Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T13:54:18.335359Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T13:54:18.347006Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"<class 'pandas.core.frame.DataFrame'>\nRangeIndex: 283 entries, 0 to 282\nData columns (total 3 columns):\n #   Column  Non-Null Count  Dtype \n---  ------  --------------  ----- \n 0   Path    283 non-null    object\n 1   Class   283 non-null    object\n 2   Label   283 non-null    object\ndtypes: object(3)\nmemory usage: 6.8+ KB\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":6},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### There are just 283 video data in video file.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Audio Processing.\n\nimport librosa\n\ndef extract_feature(file_path):\n    signal, sr = librosa.load(file_path, sr = 22100)  # sr means sample rating, it converts audio into numerical amplitudes.\n    \n    mfcc = librosa.feature.mfcc(y = signal, sr = sr, n_mfcc = 13)\n    mfcc = np.mean(mfcc.T, axis = 0)\n\n    return mfcc","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T07:59:00.659155Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T07:59:00.659443Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T07:59:00.672917Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T07:59:00.659420Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T07:59:00.672183Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":6},{"cell_type":"code","source":"X, y = [], []\n\nfor i in range(len(audio_df)):\n    file_path = audio_df.iloc[i]['Path']\n    label = audio_df.iloc[i]['Label']\n\n    feature = extract_feature(file_path)\n\n    X.append(feature)\n    y.append(label)\n\nX = np.array(X)\ny = np.array(y)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T07:59:00.676002Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T07:59:00.676268Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.332479Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T07:59:00.676244Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.331838Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":7},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **Above code will converts the audio amplitude into numerical data.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Encode label data.\n\nfrom sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder\nfrom sklearn.metrics import classification_report\n\nencoder = LabelEncoder()\ny = encoder.fit_transform(y)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.333256Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.333664Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.490737Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.333638Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.490124Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":8},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Split data with 80-20 ratio.\n\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n\nX_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size = 0.2, random_state = 101)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.491690Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.492223Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.518651Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.492172Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.518045Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":9},{"cell_type":"code","source":"from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingClassifier\n\naudio_model = GradientBoostingClassifier()\naudio_model.fit(X_train, y_train)\ny_pred = audio_model.predict(X_test)\nprint('Confusion Matrix : \\n', classification_report(y_test, y_pred))","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.519659Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.520117Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T07:59:24.092307Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T07:59:23.520081Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T07:59:24.091488Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Confusion Matrix : \n               precision    recall  f1-score   support\n\n           0       1.00      1.00      1.00        10\n           1       1.00      1.00      1.00         8\n\n    accuracy                           1.00        18\n   macro avg       1.00      1.00      1.00        18\nweighted avg       1.00      1.00      1.00        18\n\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":10},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **Gradient Boost give me realy good accuracy. Maybe bacause the data is realy low.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import cv2\n\n# Extract Frame from image.\n\ndef extract_frame(video_path, max_frames = 50):\n    cap = cv2.VideoCapture(video_path)\n    frames = []\n\n    total_frames = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_COUNT))\n    step = max(1, total_frames // max_frames)\n\n    count = 0\n    while cap.isOpened():\n        ret, frame = cap.read()\n\n        if not ret:\n            break\n\n        if count % step == 0:\n            frame = cv2.resize(frame, (64, 64))\n            frame = frame.astype('float32')\n            frame /= 255.0\n            frames.append(frame)\n            \n\n        count += 1\n\n    cap.release()\n\n    if len(frames) < max_frames:\n        padding = [np.zeros((64, 64, 3))] * (max_frames - len(frames))\n        frames.extend(padding)\n        \n    return np.array(frames[:max_frames])","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T07:59:24.093534Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T07:59:24.094006Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T07:59:24.345231Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T07:59:24.093980Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T07:59:24.344591Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":11},{"cell_type":"code","source":"X, y = [], []\n\nfor i in range(len(video_df)):\n    video_path = video_df.iloc[i]['Path']\n    label = video_df.iloc[i]['Label']\n\n    frames = extract_frame(video_path)\n    X.append(frames)\n    y.append(label)\n\nX = np.array(X)\ny = np.array(y)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T07:59:24.346137Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T07:59:24.346402Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.711589Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T07:59:24.346379Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.710599Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":12},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### **Above code will extract each video from video path, then make video into normalized image frame**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Encode label data to convert into numerical form.\n\nencode = LabelEncoder()\ny = encode.fit_transform(y)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.712799Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.713031Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.717704Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.713010Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.716748Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":13},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Split data with 80-20 ratio.\n\nX_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size = 0.2, random_state = 101)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.718632Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.718942Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.887843Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.718920Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.887181Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":14},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Shape of our data\n\nX_train.shape","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.888867Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.889170Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.894300Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.889141Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T08:00:10.893678Z"}},"outputs":[{"execution_count":15,"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":"(226, 50, 64, 64, 3)"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":15},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"#### 226 : no. of data in training dataset (X_train)\n\n#### 50 : no. frame per data\n\n#### 64, 64 : size of frame or image (64 * 64)\n\n#### 3 : colored image (RGB)","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Model training.\n\nfrom tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential\nfrom tensorflow.keras.applications import MobileNetV2\nfrom tensorflow.keras.layers import TimeDistributed, LSTM, Dense, GlobalAveragePooling2D, SimpleRNN, GRU, Flatten, Bidirectional\nfrom tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam, AdamW\n\ncnn_model = MobileNetV2(\n    weights = 'imagenet',\n    include_top = False,\n    input_shape = (64, 64, 3)\n)\n\ncnn_model.trainable = False\n    \nvideo_model = Sequential([\n    TimeDistributed(cnn_model, input_shape = (50, 64, 64, 3)),\n    TimeDistributed(GlobalAveragePooling2D()),\n    Bidirectional(GRU(128, activation = 'tanh', return_sequences = True)),\n    Bidirectional(GRU(64, activation = 'tanh')),\n    Dense(128, activation = 'tanh'),\n    Dense(2, activation = 'sigmoid')\n])\n\nvideo_model.compile(optimizer = Adam(learning_rate = 5e-4, weight_decay = 1e-3),\n                   loss = 'sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n                   metrics = ['accuracy'])\n\nvideo_model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs = 5, validation_split = 0.2)\ny_pred = video_model.predict(X_test)\ny_pred = np.argmax(y_pred, axis = 1)\n\nprint('classification report : \\n', classification_report(y_test, y_pred))","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-21T08:29:16.634058Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-21T08:29:16.634403Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-21T08:36:31.655190Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-21T08:29:16.634371Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-21T08:36:31.654502Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Epoch 1/5\n\u001b[1m6/6\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m\u001b[0m \u001b[1m282s\u001b[0m 15s/step - accuracy: 0.5825 - loss: 0.5947 - val_accuracy: 0.9130 - val_loss: 0.2540\nEpoch 2/5\n\u001b[1m6/6\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m\u001b[0m \u001b[1m3s\u001b[0m 469ms/step - accuracy: 0.9793 - loss: 0.1292 - val_accuracy: 0.9565 - val_loss: 0.1237\nEpoch 3/5\n\u001b[1m6/6\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m\u001b[0m \u001b[1m3s\u001b[0m 461ms/step - accuracy: 0.9949 - loss: 0.0351 - val_accuracy: 1.0000 - val_loss: 0.0644\nEpoch 4/5\n\u001b[1m6/6\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m\u001b[0m \u001b[1m3s\u001b[0m 472ms/step - accuracy: 1.0000 - loss: 0.0110 - val_accuracy: 1.0000 - val_loss: 0.0355\nEpoch 5/5\n\u001b[1m6/6\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m\u001b[0m \u001b[1m3s\u001b[0m 467ms/step - accuracy: 1.0000 - loss: 0.0057 - val_accuracy: 1.0000 - val_loss: 0.0271\nWARNING:tensorflow:5 out of the last 5 calls to <function TensorFlowTrainer.make_predict_function.<locals>.one_step_on_data_distributed at 0x7a24e5589c60> triggered tf.function retracing. Tracing is expensive and the excessive number of tracings could be due to (1) creating @tf.function repeatedly in a loop, (2) passing tensors with different shapes, (3) passing Python objects instead of tensors. For (1), please define your @tf.function outside of the loop. For (2), @tf.function has reduce_retracing=True option that can avoid unnecessary retracing. For (3), please refer to https://www.tensorflow.org/guide/function#controlling_retracing and https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/tf/function for  more details.\n\u001b[1m1/2\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m \u001b[1m1:13\u001b[0m 74s/stepWARNING:tensorflow:6 out of the last 6 calls to <function TensorFlowTrainer.make_predict_function.<locals>.one_step_on_data_distributed at 0x7a24e5589c60> triggered tf.function retracing. Tracing is expensive and the excessive number of tracings could be due to (1) creating @tf.function repeatedly in a loop, (2) passing tensors with different shapes, (3) passing Python objects instead of tensors. For (1), please define your @tf.function outside of the loop. For (2), @tf.